DataElement.preferredName: E-Selectin Assay Automatic Fluorescence Median Fluorescence Intensity 6 digits 2 Decimal Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The value, expressed as a number with 6 total digits with 2 digits after the decimal, for the unit of measure equal to the auto-fluorescence geometric mean fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals related to a E-Selectin Assay.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: E-selectin (610 aa, ~67 kDa) is encoded by the human SELE gene. Concepts.definition: Operating with minimal human intervention; independent of external control.

Fluorescence is a luminescence (i.e., optical phenomenon) in cold bodies, in which a molecule absorbs a high-energy photon, and re-emits it as a lower-energy (longer-wavelength) photon. The energy difference between the absorbed and emitted photons ends up as molecular vibrations (heat).
A unit of measure equal to the median fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals.
